# Cloudflare Pages (`@cloudflare/next-on-pages`)

This project deploys with **next-on-pages**, not OpenNext.

## Dashboard settings (source of truth)

| Setting | Value |
|---------|--------|
| Build command | `npx @cloudflare/next-on-pages@1` or `pnpm run build:pages` |
| Build output | `.vercel/output/static` |
| `NODE_VERSION` | ≥ 18 (use `20`) |

Enable **`nodejs_compat`** under Pages → Settings → Functions (production + preview).

## Required on every dynamic route / API

```ts
export const runtime = 'edge';
```

If the Pages build lists missing routes, run `node scripts/add-edge-runtime.mjs`.

## Do not

- Remove `runtime = 'edge'` from server routes while using next-on-pages.
- Set `package.json` `"build"` to `next-on-pages` (causes recursive builds). Use `"build": "next build"` and `build:pages` for CF.
- Reintroduce OpenNext (`build:cf`, `.open-next/`, `opennextjs-cloudflare`) without an explicit migration.

## Local verify

```bash
pnpm run build:pages && pnpm run pages:dev
```

## New server routes

Add `export const runtime = 'edge'` at the top of new `app/**/route.ts` and dynamic `page.tsx` files.
